<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-02-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-02-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="439" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Thayer</persName>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#left">No. 29.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-02-26"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 26, 1864</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of January 23, No. 44, has
                            been received; and the information it communicates relative to the
                            cotton crop in Egypt and various other subjects has been read with much
                            interest.</p>
                        <p rend="center">* * * * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">William S. Thayer</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Alexandria.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>